  "bio_raw": "Ms. Tazin Ahmed taught as full time faculty in the Department of English, Southeast University for six years (2011-2017). She has also worked as adjunct faculty in East West University and Independent University, Bangladesh. Beside these, Ms. Tazin has also worked as ESL instructor in ILAC College and Mosaic Language School in Vancouver, Canada.\nShe has completed her second Masters in Teaching English as an Additional Language(TEAL) from Simon Fraser University,Canada,and has also obtained TESOL Diploma from ILAC College, Canada which enables her to teach internationally. Ms.Tazin has six publications in referred journals and has presented a paper in 50th IATEFL conference in Birmingham under the auspices of the British Council, Bangladesh.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Socio-linguisics, Identity, Literacy, Equity, Education Policy."
  ],
  "education": [
